pmenu
=====

TUI-based power menu written in C for Linux and BSD systems.
Handles shutting down, rebooting and suspending.

Dependencies
------------
    - ncurses

Usage example
-------------
I have a Hyprland keybind to run the following:
    "$powerMenu = alacritty -o font.size=16 -T pmenu -e pmenu"
This will open up Alacritty, run pmenu and give the window an according title, so that it can be automatically floated with a windowrule.

Building
========

With nix (recommended)
------------------------
Simply run 'nix build' or 'nix run' to build according to the included flake.nix
This Github repo can also be added as a custom nix package, which is what I've done in my own config.

Manual build
------------
While meant to be built with gcc, other c compilers should work just fine since this is such a simple program.
The current build command is 'gcc --std=c99 -lmenu -lncurses -ltinfo ./src/main.c -o pmenu'
